{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":108,"text":"We conventionally divide space"},{"time":3511,"text":"into private and public realms,"},{"time":5073,"text":"and we know these legal\ndistinctions very well"},{"time":8340,"text":"because we've become experts"},{"time":10348,"text":"at protecting our private\nproperty and private space."},{"time":14208,"text":"But we're less attuned"},{"time":16112,"text":"to the nuances of the public."},{"time":19667,"text":"What translates generic public\nspace into qualitative space?"},{"time":23590,"text":"I mean, this is something"},{"time":24996,"text":"that our studio has been working on"},{"time":26821,"text":"for the past decade."},{"time":28329,"text":"And we're doing this\nthrough some case studies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":30592,"text":"A large chunk of our work"},{"time":32081,"text":"has been put into transforming"},{"time":33621,"text":"this neglected industrial ruin"},{"time":36417,"text":"into a viable post-industrial space"},{"time":39490,"text":"that looks forward and backward"},{"time":40991,"text":"at the same time."},{"time":42252,"text":"And another huge chunk of our work"},{"time":44754,"text":"has gone into making relevant"},{"time":46792,"text":"a site that's grown\nout of sync with its time."},{"time":49488,"text":"We've been working\non democratizing Lincoln Center"},{"time":52532,"text":"for a public that doesn't\nusually have $300"},{"time":56250,"text":"to spend on an opera ticket."},{"time":60015,"text":"So we've been eating, drinking,"},{"time":61706,"text":"thinking, living public space"},{"time":64000,"text":"for quite a long time."},{"time":65971,"text":"And it's taught us really one thing,"},{"time":68240,"text":"and that is to truly\nmake good public space,"},{"time":72208,"text":"you have to erase the distinctions"},{"time":75458,"text":"between architecture, urbanism,"},{"time":78083,"text":"landscape, media design"},{"time":79958,"text":"and so on."},{"time":81542,"text":"It really goes beyond distinction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":83571,"text":"Now we're moving onto Washington, D.C."},{"time":86625,"text":"and we're working\non another transformation,"},{"time":88958,"text":"and that is for the existing\nHirshhorn Museum"},{"time":91583,"text":"that's sited"},{"time":93208,"text":"on the most revered\npublic space in America,"},{"time":95500,"text":"the National Mall."},{"time":98433,"text":"The Mall is a symbol"},{"time":100000,"text":"of American democracy."},{"time":102833,"text":"And what's fantastic is that this symbol"},{"time":105833,"text":"is not a thing, it's not an image,"},{"time":108042,"text":"it's not an artifact,"},{"time":109750,"text":"actually it's a space,"},{"time":111458,"text":"and it's kind of just defined\nby a line of buildings"},{"time":114308,"text":"on either side."}]},{"cues":[{"time":116339,"text":"It's a space where citizens\ncan voice their discontent"},{"time":120083,"text":"and show their power."},{"time":121376,"text":"It's a place where pivotal\nmoments in American history"},{"time":124292,"text":"have taken place."},{"time":126448,"text":"And they're inscribed in there forever --"},{"time":128854,"text":"like the march on Washington\nfor jobs and freedom"},{"time":131233,"text":"and the great speech that Martin\nLuther King gave there."},{"time":134325,"text":"The Vietnam protests,\nthe commemoration of all that died"},{"time":138708,"text":"in the pandemic of AIDS,"},{"time":140750,"text":"the march for women's reproductive rights,"},{"time":143292,"text":"right up until almost the present."},{"time":146750,"text":"The Mall is the greatest civic stage"},{"time":149912,"text":"in this country for dissent."},{"time":153583,"text":"And it's synonymous with free speech,"},{"time":157471,"text":"even if you're not sure what it\nis that you have to say."},{"time":160162,"text":"It may just be a place\nfor civic commiseration."}]},{"cues":[{"time":165192,"text":"There is a huge disconnect, we believe,"},{"time":168833,"text":"between the communicative\nand discursive space of the Mall"},{"time":173000,"text":"and the museums that line\nit to either side."},{"time":177042,"text":"And that is that those\nmuseums are usually passive,"},{"time":180667,"text":"they have passive relationships\nbetween the museum"},{"time":184042,"text":"as the presenter and the audience,"},{"time":185686,"text":"as the receiver of information."},{"time":187958,"text":"And so you can see dinosaurs"},{"time":189708,"text":"and insects and collections of locomotives"},{"time":193792,"text":"and all of that,"},{"time":195117,"text":"but you're really not involved;"},{"time":196648,"text":"you're being talked to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":198292,"text":"When Richard Koshalek took\nover as director of the Hirshhorn"},{"time":202995,"text":"in 2009,"},{"time":204792,"text":"he was determined to take advantage"},{"time":207208,"text":"of the fact that this museum was sited"},{"time":210458,"text":"at the most unique place:"},{"time":212208,"text":"at the seat of power in the U.S."},{"time":214083,"text":"And while art and politics"},{"time":216292,"text":"are inherently and implicitly\ntogether always and all the time,"},{"time":221750,"text":"there could be some very\nspecial relationship"},{"time":225917,"text":"that could be forged\nhere in its uniqueness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":229833,"text":"The question is, is it possible ultimately"},{"time":232458,"text":"for art to insert itself"},{"time":234208,"text":"into the dialogue of national\nand world affairs?"},{"time":237333,"text":"And could the museum be\nan agent of cultural diplomacy?"},{"time":241202,"text":"There are over 180 embassies\nin Washington D.C."},{"time":246263,"text":"There are over 500 think tanks."},{"time":249250,"text":"There should be a way"},{"time":250750,"text":"of harnessing all of that intellectual\nand global energy"},{"time":253667,"text":"into, and somehow through, the museum."},{"time":255817,"text":"There should be some kind of brain trust."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258896,"text":"So the Hirshhorn, as we began\nto think about it,"},{"time":262208,"text":"and as we evolved the mission,"},{"time":264708,"text":"with Richard and his team --"},{"time":266542,"text":"it's really his life blood."},{"time":268667,"text":"But beyond exhibiting contemporary art,"},{"time":272752,"text":"the Hirshhorn will become a public forum,"},{"time":275542,"text":"a place of discourse"},{"time":277667,"text":"for issues around arts,"},{"time":279875,"text":"culture, politics and policy."},{"time":284958,"text":"It would have the global reach\nof the World Economic Forum."},{"time":288958,"text":"It would have the interdisciplinarity\nof the TED Conference."},{"time":291840,"text":"It would have the informality\nof the town square."},{"time":296298,"text":"And for this new initiative,"},{"time":298227,"text":"the Hirshhorn would have to expand"},{"time":300042,"text":"or appropriate a site"},{"time":301419,"text":"for a contemporary, deployable structure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":304313,"text":"This is it. This is the Hirshhorn --"},{"time":306052,"text":"so a 230-foot-diameter concrete doughnut"},{"time":309167,"text":"designed in the early '70s"},{"time":311375,"text":"by Gordon Bunshaft."},{"time":313127,"text":"It's hulking, it's silent,"},{"time":314417,"text":"it's cloistered, it's arrogant,"},{"time":316167,"text":"it's a design challenge."},{"time":318500,"text":"Architects love to hate it."},{"time":320073,"text":"One redeeming feature"},{"time":322083,"text":"is it's lifted up off the ground"},{"time":323792,"text":"and it's got this void,"},{"time":325542,"text":"and it's got an empty core"},{"time":327167,"text":"kind of in the spirit and that facade"},{"time":330083,"text":"very much corporate and federal style."}]},{"cues":[{"time":333833,"text":"And around that space,"},{"time":335750,"text":"the ring is actually galleries."},{"time":337292,"text":"Very, very difficult\nto mount shows in there."},{"time":339917,"text":"When the Hirshhorn opened,"},{"time":341875,"text":"Ada Louise Huxstable,\nthe New York Times critic,"},{"time":344185,"text":"had some choice words:"},{"time":345696,"text":"\"Neo-penitentiary modern.\""},{"time":347498,"text":"\"A maimed monument and a maimed Mall"},{"time":350357,"text":"for a maimed collection.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":351792,"text":"Almost four decades later,"},{"time":353548,"text":"how will this building expand"},{"time":355292,"text":"for a new progressive program?"},{"time":357321,"text":"Where would it go?"},{"time":358833,"text":"It can't go in the Mall."},{"time":360075,"text":"There is no space there."},{"time":361332,"text":"It can't go in the courtyard."},{"time":362875,"text":"It's already taken up by landscape\nand by sculptures."},{"time":368083,"text":"Well there's always the hole."},{"time":369488,"text":"But how could it take\nthe space of that hole"},{"time":374000,"text":"and not be buried in it invisibly?"},{"time":376000,"text":"How could it become iconic?"},{"time":377750,"text":"And what language would it take?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":381298,"text":"The Hirshhorn sits\namong the Mall's monumental institutions."},{"time":384500,"text":"Most are neoclassical, heavy and opaque,"},{"time":387344,"text":"made of stone or concrete."},{"time":390142,"text":"And the question is,"},{"time":392032,"text":"if one inhabits that space,"},{"time":393448,"text":"what is the material of the Mall?"},{"time":396810,"text":"It has to be different\nfrom the buildings there."},{"time":399458,"text":"It has to be something entirely different."},{"time":401482,"text":"It has to be air."},{"time":403270,"text":"In our imagination, it has to be light."},{"time":405792,"text":"It has to be ephemeral.\nIt has to be formless."},{"time":408007,"text":"And it has to be free."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410031,"text":"(Video)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":421387,"text":"So this is the big idea."},{"time":424518,"text":"It's a giant airbag."},{"time":427083,"text":"The expansion takes\nthe shape of its container"},{"time":430738,"text":"and it oozes out wherever it can --"},{"time":432477,"text":"the top and sides."},{"time":434500,"text":"But more poetically,"},{"time":436250,"text":"we like to think of the structure"},{"time":438292,"text":"as inhaling the democratic\nair of the Mall,"},{"time":440364,"text":"bringing it into itself."},{"time":444125,"text":"The before and the after."}]},{"cues":[{"time":448096,"text":"It was dubbed \"the bubble\" by the press."},{"time":451250,"text":"That was the lounge."},{"time":453792,"text":"It's basically one big volume of air"},{"time":456754,"text":"that just oozes out in every direction."},{"time":459042,"text":"The membrane is translucent."},{"time":461075,"text":"It's made of silcon-coated glass fiber."},{"time":464764,"text":"And it's inflated twice a year\nfor one month at a time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":468856,"text":"This is the view from the inside."},{"time":472041,"text":"So you might have been wondering"},{"time":473887,"text":"how in the world"},{"time":475865,"text":"did we get this approved\nby the federal government."},{"time":478318,"text":"It had to be approved\nby actually two agencies."},{"time":482198,"text":"And one is there to preserve"},{"time":486083,"text":"the dignity and sanctity of the Mall."},{"time":488448,"text":"I blush whenever I show this."},{"time":491181,"text":"It is yours to interpret."}]},{"cues":[{"time":495000,"text":"But one thing I can say"},{"time":497042,"text":"is that it's a combination"},{"time":499500,"text":"of iconoclasm"},{"time":501750,"text":"and adoration."},{"time":505377,"text":"There was also some creative\ninterpretation involved."},{"time":508493,"text":"The Congressional Buildings Act of 1910"},{"time":511417,"text":"limits the height of buildings in D.C."},{"time":513375,"text":"to 130 feet,"},{"time":515333,"text":"except for spires, towers,\ndomes and minarets."},{"time":518208,"text":"This pretty much exempts monuments\nof the church and state."},{"time":522875,"text":"And the bubble is 153 ft."},{"time":526000,"text":"That's the Pantheon next to it."},{"time":528625,"text":"It's about 1.2 million cubic\nfeet of compressed air."},{"time":531917,"text":"And so we argued it"},{"time":533833,"text":"on the merits of being a dome."}]},{"cues":[{"time":535833,"text":"So there it is,"},{"time":537917,"text":"very stately,"},{"time":539091,"text":"among all the stately\nbuildings in the Mall."},{"time":542542,"text":"And while this Hirshhorn\nis not landmarked,"},{"time":545583,"text":"it's very, very historically sensitive."},{"time":547958,"text":"And so we couldn't really\ntouch its surfaces."},{"time":550333,"text":"We couldn't leave any traces behind."},{"time":552072,"text":"So we strained it from the edges,"},{"time":554250,"text":"and we held it by cables."},{"time":556375,"text":"It's a study of some bondage techniques,"},{"time":559750,"text":"which are actually very important"},{"time":561433,"text":"because it's hit by wind all the time."},{"time":563358,"text":"There's one permanent\nsteel ring at the top,"},{"time":565473,"text":"but it can't be seen\nfrom any vantage point on the Mall."}]},{"cues":[{"time":568188,"text":"There are also some restrictions"},{"time":570375,"text":"about how much it could be lit."},{"time":571876,"text":"It glows from within, it's translucent."},{"time":573917,"text":"But it can't be more lit than the Capitol"},{"time":577083,"text":"or some of the monuments."},{"time":578500,"text":"So it's down the hierarchy on lighting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":580880,"text":"So it comes to the site twice a year."},{"time":583000,"text":"It's taken off the delivery truck."},{"time":585958,"text":"It's hoisted."},{"time":587458,"text":"And then it's inflated"},{"time":589750,"text":"with this low-pressure air."},{"time":591500,"text":"And then it's restrained with the cables."},{"time":593477,"text":"And then it's ballasted\nwith water at the very bottom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":596667,"text":"This is a very strange moment"},{"time":600792,"text":"where we were asked\nby the bureaucracy at the Mall"},{"time":603208,"text":"how much time would it take to install."},{"time":606417,"text":"And we said, well the first\nerection would take one week."},{"time":609156,"text":"And they really connected with that idea."},{"time":612500,"text":"And then it was really\neasy all the way through."},{"time":616500,"text":"So we didn't really have\nthat many hurdles, I have to say,"},{"time":620583,"text":"with the government\nand all the authorities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":622655,"text":"But some of the toughest hurdles"},{"time":624203,"text":"have been the technical ones."},{"time":625708,"text":"This is the warp and weft."},{"time":627000,"text":"This is a point cloud."},{"time":629042,"text":"There are extreme pressures."},{"time":631167,"text":"This is a very, very unusual building"},{"time":632953,"text":"in that there's no gravity load,"},{"time":634875,"text":"but there's load in every direction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":636614,"text":"And I'm just going to zip\nthrough these slides."},{"time":641167,"text":"And this is the space in action."},{"time":644292,"text":"So flexible interior for discussions,"},{"time":647125,"text":"just like this, but in the round --"},{"time":649458,"text":"luminous and reconfigurable."},{"time":650917,"text":"Could be used for anything,"},{"time":653333,"text":"for performances, films,"},{"time":655083,"text":"for installations."},{"time":657625,"text":"And the very first program"},{"time":660042,"text":"will be one of cultural\ndialogue and diplomacy"},{"time":662257,"text":"organized in partnership"},{"time":663542,"text":"with the Council on Foreign Relations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":666167,"text":"Form and content are together here."},{"time":667917,"text":"The bubble is an anti-monument."},{"time":670583,"text":"The ideals of participatory democracy"},{"time":673125,"text":"are represented through suppleness"},{"time":675250,"text":"rather than rigidity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":676696,"text":"Art and politics"},{"time":678125,"text":"occupy an ambiguous site\noutside the museum walls,"},{"time":681765,"text":"but inside of the museum's core,"},{"time":685358,"text":"blending its air"},{"time":687208,"text":"with the democratic air of the Mall."},{"time":689575,"text":"And the bubble will inflate"},{"time":695125,"text":"hopefully for the first time"},{"time":696750,"text":"at the end of 2013."}]},{"cues":[{"time":698958,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":701458,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}